sql:
SELECT housing_med, rent_med, inventory
FROM housing_market
WHERE year = 2002;

external_knowledge:
This query assumes that the economic indicators and housing market data are correctly associated with the state of Texas through their respective data source IDs. Texas is one of the 50 states in the United States; 
The economic indicators include various metrics that describe the economic health of a region, such as unemployment rate, average wage, and GDP; 
Housing market data encompasses statistics related to the real estate market, including median housing prices and sales volume.

sql:
SELECT year, housing_med, rent_med
FROM housing_market
ORDER BY year ASC;

SELECT AVG(housing_med) AS avg_median_housing_price
FROM housing_market
WHERE year = 2001;
